1
00:01:17,467 --> 00:01:20,280
Dear brothers and sisters.

2
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:22,053
Today...

3
00:01:22,053 --> 00:01:24,534
We gather to pray

4
00:01:24,534 --> 00:01:27,114
for the eternal rest

5
00:01:27,114 --> 00:01:29,433
of the late Kim Mi Ran, Julia.

6
00:01:32,548 --> 00:01:35,394
Though her life on this earth has ended,

7
00:01:36,294 --> 00:01:40,000
let us remember that
a new life has begun in heaven,

8
00:01:41,573 --> 00:01:45,806
and fill our hearts with hope.

9
00:01:48,094 --> 00:01:50,827
Julia was a wonderful mother,

10
00:01:50,827 --> 00:01:52,681
wife, and...

11
00:01:52,681 --> 00:01:54,401
friend.

12
00:01:56,468 --> 00:01:57,867
This means

13
00:01:57,867 --> 00:02:01,341
that Julia was never alone,

14
00:02:02,034 --> 00:02:04,180
and even now,

15
00:02:04,180 --> 00:02:08,134
she is being accompanied by her loving husband,

16
00:02:08,134 --> 00:02:09,714
daughter,

17
00:02:09,714 --> 00:02:11,114
son,

18
00:02:11,628 --> 00:02:16,514
and all those who cherished her.

19
00:02:19,357 --> 00:02:22,069
Letting go of someone we love is

20
00:02:22,069 --> 00:02:25,197
deeply painful and difficult.

21
00:02:25,771 --> 00:02:29,744
But the Lord gives us hope.

22
00:02:31,257 --> 00:02:33,577
We pray that the Lord may comfort us

23
00:02:34,177 --> 00:02:37,443
and grant peace

24
00:02:38,037 --> 00:02:42,890
and grace to all who remain.

25
00:02:43,517 --> 00:02:45,077
Amen.

26
00:02:52,316 --> 00:02:53,957
I'll get going.

27
00:02:53,957 --> 00:02:55,617
Thank you for coming.

28
00:02:56,390 --> 00:02:57,681
Gosh...

29
00:02:57,681 --> 00:02:59,814
My poor sister.

30
00:02:59,814 --> 00:03:00,933
Bye.

31
00:03:00,933 --> 00:03:03,753
She went through so much, and now she's gone...

32
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:08,366
You poor things.

33
00:03:15,856 --> 00:03:17,496
Hello?

34
00:03:17,496 --> 00:03:19,969
Yeah, sure.

35
00:03:19,969 --> 00:03:21,910
He looks like a walking corpse.

36
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:24,634
As thank you gifts? Let me think...

37
00:03:24,634 --> 00:03:27,448
Jun Kyung, take good care of him.

38
00:03:28,095 --> 00:03:29,119
Okay.

39
00:03:29,119 --> 00:03:30,847
- Take care, you two.
- 30-count is more...

40
00:03:30,847 --> 00:03:32,589
practical and durable...

41
00:03:32,589 --> 00:03:35,942
40-count is softer and more premium...

42
00:03:35,942 --> 00:03:38,202
Oh, you're having a first birthday party.

43
00:03:51,416 --> 00:03:53,569
They don't look that sad.

44
00:03:55,149 --> 00:03:56,549
It's like...

45
00:03:57,423 --> 00:03:59,963
they're just here to take care of business.

46
00:04:00,596 --> 00:04:03,536
Everyone grieves in their own way.

47
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:09,381
[Handong Catholic Church]

48
00:04:09,381 --> 00:04:11,107
I'll get going.

49
00:04:13,557 --> 00:04:15,590
- Take care.
- Thank you.

50
00:04:27,233 --> 00:04:29,579
A lot of people came.

51
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:35,052
Yeah.

52
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:40,786
It would've been nice
if they'd come while she was alive.

53
00:04:45,562 --> 00:04:48,186
[The late Kim Mi Ran]

54
00:04:50,821 --> 00:04:53,121
[The late Kim Mi Ran, Julia]

55
00:05:05,380 --> 00:05:06,826
Let's go.

56
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:09,946
Your mom needs to rest now.

57
00:05:26,577 --> 00:05:29,070
I'll stay a little longer with Jun Seo.

58
00:05:47,877 --> 00:05:50,204
Don't be sad. I'm here.

59
00:05:58,991 --> 00:06:00,743
Don't lie! You saw her!

60
00:06:00,743 --> 00:06:02,800
What are you talking about? I didn't!

61
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,902
You did!

62
00:06:03,902 --> 00:06:06,112
There's been a misunderstanding.
Please calm down.

63
00:06:06,112 --> 00:06:07,966
Then let's check the security camera.

64
00:06:07,966 --> 00:06:09,946
- Hey...
- Let's check it now!

65
00:06:09,946 --> 00:06:12,879
- Sir, please calm down.
- Hey!

66
00:06:12,879 --> 00:06:15,251
This pervert was staring at my girl's legs!

67
00:06:15,251 --> 00:06:16,906
Seo Jun Seo!

68
00:06:20,459 --> 00:06:22,299
What did I do wrong?

69
00:06:22,299 --> 00:06:24,833
Did you really have to do that here?
You embarrassed me.

70
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:28,219
Did you really have to wear
such a skirt to a place like this?

71
00:06:32,099 --> 00:06:33,733
What?

72
00:06:33,733 --> 00:06:37,032
That outfit isn't appropriate
for a place like this.

73
00:06:38,861 --> 00:06:41,479
I didn't dress like this
because of where we are.

74
00:06:41,479 --> 00:06:43,541
This is the real me.

75
00:06:45,141 --> 00:06:47,094
I hate it!

76
00:06:47,094 --> 00:06:50,027
I hate that you dress like that every day.

77
00:06:54,181 --> 00:06:57,514
I hate that you post outfits like that
on social media, too.

78
00:06:57,514 --> 00:07:00,734
And it pisses me off when guys
hit on you after seeing that.

79
00:07:04,637 --> 00:07:07,164
You really make me feel so alone.

80
00:07:17,048 --> 00:07:18,448
Hey, Yoon Sol.

81
00:07:19,688 --> 00:07:21,088
Yoon Sol!

82
00:07:34,634 --> 00:07:36,140
I ruined it.

83
00:07:40,837 --> 00:07:43,084
My mom's last day.

84
00:07:50,883 --> 00:07:53,429
I thought there'd be another day.

85
00:08:05,254 --> 00:08:07,240
Your mom and I...

86
00:08:07,834 --> 00:08:09,974
We weren't anything special, but...

87
00:08:11,421 --> 00:08:14,060
I thought we'd be okay, just like this...

88
00:08:15,047 --> 00:08:17,107
Grow old together.

89
00:08:19,565 --> 00:08:22,131
Take trips sometimes to nice places.

90
00:08:24,298 --> 00:08:27,548
Eat ice cream
while watching the sunset side by side.

91
00:08:27,548 --> 00:08:29,248
Sing songs together.

92
00:08:32,041 --> 00:08:35,068
Even ride the yacht
your mom always wanted to try.

93
00:08:40,824 --> 00:08:43,464
It's sad when someone dies, but...

94
00:08:45,198 --> 00:08:47,630
All the things they wanted to do...

95
00:08:49,289 --> 00:08:52,348
All the things your mom
and I planned to do together...

96
00:08:56,242 --> 00:08:59,582
It feels like all of that disappears too.

97
00:09:08,859 --> 00:09:12,025
Excuse me, could you pull over for a moment?

98
00:09:13,606 --> 00:09:15,246
What's wrong?

99
00:09:23,337 --> 00:09:25,170
Dad?

100
00:09:25,170 --> 00:09:26,570
Go first.

101
00:10:46,999 --> 00:10:48,789
<i>The person you're calling is unavailable.</i>

102
00:10:48,789 --> 00:10:51,189
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

103
00:13:29,823 --> 00:13:31,422
Is everything all right?

104
00:13:34,143 --> 00:13:38,263
Her cervix is dilating well,
but the contractions are irregular.

105
00:13:38,263 --> 00:13:40,443
Hey, I'm talking about you.

106
00:13:40,443 --> 00:13:42,609
Are you okay?

107
00:13:45,714 --> 00:13:47,561
Of course I am.

108
00:13:49,215 --> 00:13:52,260
There you go again... pretending.

109
00:13:52,260 --> 00:13:55,429
How could you possibly be okay?

110
00:13:55,429 --> 00:13:58,755
The neighbor's guitar was kind of comforting.

111
00:13:59,554 --> 00:14:01,187
What are you talking about?

112
00:14:02,996 --> 00:14:06,215
When someone is born, someone else dies.

113
00:14:08,836 --> 00:14:11,363
Someone pays me a salary,

114
00:14:11,363 --> 00:14:13,049
and I just do my job.

115
00:14:13,995 --> 00:14:15,186
You're really something else.

116
00:14:15,186 --> 00:14:18,159
I keep my work and personal life
strictly separate.

117
00:14:18,888 --> 00:14:20,288
Got it?

118
00:14:20,861 --> 00:14:23,601
Honey, should I step outside?

119
00:14:23,601 --> 00:14:25,648
Please don't go.

120
00:14:25,648 --> 00:14:28,009
You can't stay like this. Push.

121
00:14:29,123 --> 00:14:31,339
Breathe. Don't hold it in.

122
00:14:31,339 --> 00:14:32,756
Honey, breathe!

123
00:14:32,756 --> 00:14:34,779
Your wife needs to breathe, not you.

124
00:14:34,779 --> 00:14:37,016
Honey! I think I'm dying!

125
00:14:37,016 --> 00:14:39,729
You're not going to die. Don't worry.

126
00:14:39,729 --> 00:14:41,946
There's no one who can give birth for you.

127
00:14:41,946 --> 00:14:45,112
Are you going to look that weak
in front of your daughter?

128
00:14:48,036 --> 00:14:51,174
You don't want to end up the kind of mom

129
00:14:51,174 --> 00:14:53,749
who loses her legs
in a rainy car accident, right?

130
00:14:56,349 --> 00:14:58,522
Or a mom who argues with her daughter...

131
00:14:59,329 --> 00:15:01,289
And dies of a brain hemorrhage...

132
00:15:03,623 --> 00:15:05,489
Without ever making up with her.

133
00:15:05,489 --> 00:15:07,935
You don't want to be that kind of mother.

134
00:15:08,488 --> 00:15:10,588
What are you even talking about?

135
00:15:14,769 --> 00:15:16,275
[Reception Office]

136
00:15:22,329 --> 00:15:23,942
Hey.

137
00:15:23,942 --> 00:15:27,116
You said you keep work
and personal life strictly separate.

138
00:15:27,116 --> 00:15:30,379
The whole hospital is buzzing.

139
00:15:30,379 --> 00:15:33,329
They say Dr. Seo tried a new delivery method.

140
00:15:34,269 --> 00:15:37,002
The patient must've been really confused.

141
00:15:37,002 --> 00:15:40,176
You kept shouting "daughter" when it was a son.

142
00:15:40,176 --> 00:15:42,102
Bet the baby was confused too.

143
00:15:42,102 --> 00:15:44,082
Like, "Mom, was I a girl?"

144
00:15:45,562 --> 00:15:48,609
I'm not in the mood for jokes.

145
00:15:49,676 --> 00:15:51,549
I'm not joking.

146
00:15:52,142 --> 00:15:54,422
I was giving you a compliment.

147
00:15:56,976 --> 00:15:59,502
Even cold-blooded Seo Jun Kyung

148
00:15:59,502 --> 00:16:01,795
has a heart after all.

149
00:16:03,376 --> 00:16:06,622
Yeah, you might've looked a little crazy...

150
00:16:06,622 --> 00:16:08,069
But so what?

151
00:16:08,709 --> 00:16:10,222
You did well.

152
00:16:16,322 --> 00:16:18,835
Did my mom love me?

153
00:16:20,192 --> 00:16:21,964
When I think about it,

154
00:16:23,478 --> 00:16:25,809
I don't think

155
00:16:25,809 --> 00:16:29,096
I have ever heard her say she loved me.

156
00:16:29,096 --> 00:16:30,396
Gosh.

157
00:16:30,396 --> 00:16:32,536
You raise daughters with all your heart,

158
00:16:32,536 --> 00:16:34,922
and this is what they end up saying.

159
00:16:36,170 --> 00:16:39,302
Have you ever told your mom you loved her?

160
00:16:42,743 --> 00:16:46,822
I thought I'd at least get to share
40 more meals with my mom.

161
00:16:50,716 --> 00:16:52,542
But look.

162
00:16:53,841 --> 00:16:56,395
She stayed irresponsible till the very end.

163
00:16:58,910 --> 00:17:00,690
Hey, I'm never ever

164
00:17:00,690 --> 00:17:04,902
going to die before my daughter.

165
00:17:06,676 --> 00:17:08,223
That's impressive.

166
00:17:08,223 --> 00:17:11,186
A mom whose goal is to outlive her daughter.

167
00:17:11,186 --> 00:17:12,214
Pretty great, huh?

168
00:17:12,214 --> 00:17:14,763
- I think I'm amazing.
- You really are.

169
00:17:15,910 --> 00:17:18,569
Jun Kyung, that's enough drinking.

170
00:17:19,410 --> 00:17:21,350
You're heading home already?

171
00:17:21,350 --> 00:17:22,942
Look at this.

172
00:17:22,942 --> 00:17:26,903
My daughters are blowing up my phone.

173
00:17:26,903 --> 00:17:28,283
Don't answer it.

174
00:17:28,283 --> 00:17:30,649
Don't go.

175
00:17:30,649 --> 00:17:32,576
Hi, sweetie.

176
00:17:33,596 --> 00:17:35,430
Yeah.

177
00:17:35,430 --> 00:17:37,742
Is your Dad drunk?

178
00:17:45,274 --> 00:17:49,905
[Mom]

179
00:18:07,916 --> 00:18:10,408
[My daughter]

180
00:18:24,629 --> 00:18:26,029
Mom.

181
00:18:38,181 --> 00:18:39,581
<i>Jun Kyung?</i>

182
00:18:40,940 --> 00:18:42,421
<i>I was bringing in the laundry.</i>

183
00:18:42,421 --> 00:18:44,067
<i>It's raining now.</i>

184
00:18:48,481 --> 00:18:52,140
<i>You forgot again? You're so scatterbrained.</i>

185
00:18:52,140 --> 00:18:54,033
<i>Where did you put it?</i>

186
00:18:56,346 --> 00:18:57,451
<i>Mom, where are you now?</i>

187
00:18:57,451 --> 00:18:59,071
<i>Almost there.</i>

188
00:18:59,071 --> 00:19:01,028
<i>Stop rushing me.</i>

189
00:19:01,028 --> 00:19:03,412
<i>I told you to send it by courier. It's raining.</i>

190
00:19:03,412 --> 00:19:05,592
<i>A courier? Do you know how much that costs?</i>

191
00:19:05,592 --> 00:19:07,501
<i>- I'll be faster.
- So where are you now?</i>

192
00:19:07,501 --> 00:19:10,834
<i>- I just passed Howon Station.
- Okay, I'll head out now.</i>

193
00:19:30,081 --> 00:19:32,114
<i>Mom, where are you?</i>

194
00:19:34,148 --> 00:19:36,208
<i>Hurry up.</i>

195
00:20:33,788 --> 00:20:36,001
I told you not to come.

196
00:20:41,373 --> 00:20:44,066
I told you not to come...

197
00:20:48,993 --> 00:20:51,092
since it's raining.

198
00:20:54,393 --> 00:20:56,506
Since it's raining.

199
00:20:57,426 --> 00:21:00,339
I told you not to come.

200
00:21:11,259 --> 00:21:13,656
It's not your fault.

201
00:21:16,330 --> 00:21:18,216
It's not your fault.

202
00:21:19,803 --> 00:21:21,262
Don't cry.

203
00:21:21,262 --> 00:21:23,369
Don't cry, Jun Kyung.

204
00:21:24,670 --> 00:21:26,622
It's not your fault.

205
00:21:56,451 --> 00:21:58,309
- It's raining again.
- I know.

206
00:21:58,309 --> 00:21:59,818
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

207
00:22:00,577 --> 00:22:02,350
What should we grab for dinner?

208
00:22:31,078 --> 00:22:32,932
Hey!

209
00:22:32,932 --> 00:22:34,624
Seo Jun Seo!

210
00:22:35,291 --> 00:22:36,691
Hey!

211
00:22:39,519 --> 00:22:41,406
[Fast-Pitch Ball Game]

212
00:22:52,660 --> 00:22:54,706
Please, just let me hit it once.

213
00:22:55,621 --> 00:22:57,120
Just once!

214
00:23:03,481 --> 00:23:05,154
Geez...

215
00:23:08,025 --> 00:23:09,871
Is anyone...

216
00:23:10,624 --> 00:23:12,337
Is anyone there?

217
00:23:13,197 --> 00:23:14,937
- Please.
- What's going on?

218
00:23:14,937 --> 00:23:16,983
Mister, please help me.

219
00:23:17,856 --> 00:23:20,969
- I can't move my neck.
- What's going on in the rain?

220
00:24:03,640 --> 00:24:05,347
You again.

221
00:24:06,521 --> 00:24:07,921
Yeah.

222
00:24:10,267 --> 00:24:11,291
Oh my.

223
00:24:11,291 --> 00:24:13,757
I forgot my door code.

224
00:24:13,757 --> 00:24:15,467
Funny, huh?

225
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:20,141
You can ask your husband to open it.

226
00:24:20,141 --> 00:24:21,973
My husband?

227
00:24:24,001 --> 00:24:25,401
Oh, right.

228
00:24:26,747 --> 00:24:28,760
Oh, my husband...

229
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:30,304
He's on a business trip.

230
00:24:30,304 --> 00:24:32,467
Like, far away.

231
00:24:34,401 --> 00:24:37,207
Then you can call and ask him.

232
00:24:43,293 --> 00:24:45,953
Oh, perfect timing.

233
00:24:48,460 --> 00:24:51,053
Where did I put my phone?

234
00:24:57,114 --> 00:24:59,400
- Oh no.
- It's ringing.

235
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:00,800
Here.

236
00:25:06,127 --> 00:25:08,427
Hey, what was our door code?

237
00:25:14,287 --> 00:25:15,933
The ER?

238
00:25:23,707 --> 00:25:25,293
Which hospital?

239
00:25:28,561 --> 00:25:30,427
Okay, I'm coming.

240
00:25:43,139 --> 00:25:45,013
I'll drive you.

241
00:25:45,013 --> 00:25:46,972
I'm okay.

242
00:25:46,972 --> 00:25:49,152
- Isn't it urgent?
- It is.

243
00:25:52,573 --> 00:25:53,973
Get in here.

244
00:25:56,386 --> 00:25:58,526
What?

245
00:25:58,526 --> 00:26:01,105
- Whose car is that?
- Mine.

246
00:26:01,793 --> 00:26:03,395
Let's go.

247
00:26:03,395 --> 00:26:06,779
- You said the ER, right?
- Yeah...

248
00:26:06,779 --> 00:26:09,258
- It's my car.
- Wait a second.

249
00:26:09,258 --> 00:26:10,658
That hurts.

250
00:26:13,398 --> 00:26:14,798
Oh, hi.

251
00:26:15,633 --> 00:26:17,685
What, did you drink?

252
00:26:18,539 --> 00:26:20,596
Nice going.

253
00:26:20,596 --> 00:26:22,729
So your paper is about
baseball fusion or something?

254
00:26:22,729 --> 00:26:24,836
Don't joke around. I'm in this much pain.

255
00:26:24,836 --> 00:26:26,539
The nurse already told me everything.

256
00:26:26,539 --> 00:26:28,103
You hurt yourself swinging at nothing.

257
00:26:28,103 --> 00:26:31,049
And they said you can take
the neck brace off soon.

258
00:26:31,049 --> 00:26:32,766
I'm still not okay. I almost died.

259
00:26:32,766 --> 00:26:34,859
The painkillers saved me.

260
00:26:35,809 --> 00:26:37,404
I was stupid to call you.

261
00:26:37,404 --> 00:26:38,786
You called me because of the bill, huh?

262
00:26:38,786 --> 00:26:41,590
No. Don't pay it. Not a cent.

263
00:26:42,729 --> 00:26:45,889
Alright, then I'll go back with my wallet.

264
00:26:45,889 --> 00:26:48,369
How can someone be so annoying?

265
00:26:48,369 --> 00:26:49,769
Gosh.

266
00:26:56,988 --> 00:26:58,388
I'm sorry.

267
00:26:59,055 --> 00:27:00,728
No.

268
00:27:00,728 --> 00:27:02,461
I'm sorry.

269
00:27:06,141 --> 00:27:08,601
No, I really am.

270
00:27:10,134 --> 00:27:11,558
Why are you crying?

271
00:27:11,558 --> 00:27:14,244
Don't cry, baby.

272
00:27:14,244 --> 00:27:15,908
Don't cry.

273
00:27:15,908 --> 00:27:18,615
This is my fault.

274
00:27:18,615 --> 00:27:20,155
Look at me.

275
00:27:20,155 --> 00:27:21,754
Sol, look at me.

276
00:27:22,421 --> 00:27:24,601
Don't cry.

277
00:27:25,495 --> 00:27:27,668
What do I do...

278
00:27:29,454 --> 00:27:31,565
- I think I really love you.
- Hug me.

279
00:27:31,565 --> 00:27:33,308
I love you more.

280
00:27:34,289 --> 00:27:35,901
Love you.

281
00:27:40,678 --> 00:27:42,484
Hello, Sol?

282
00:27:46,664 --> 00:27:48,444
Hello, sis.

283
00:27:49,792 --> 00:27:51,572
Hi.

284
00:27:51,572 --> 00:27:52,972
Hi.

285
00:27:53,818 --> 00:27:55,365
By the way,

286
00:27:55,365 --> 00:27:56,555
who is this?

287
00:27:56,555 --> 00:27:57,998
Huh?

288
00:27:58,625 --> 00:28:00,711
This is... well...

289
00:28:03,792 --> 00:28:05,838
May I ask your name?

290
00:28:05,838 --> 00:28:07,665
I'm Ju Do Hyun.

291
00:28:07,665 --> 00:28:10,461
This is Ju Do Hyun. He lives next door.

292
00:28:10,461 --> 00:28:13,038
Why would the guy next door

293
00:28:13,038 --> 00:28:14,538
come here at this hour?

294
00:28:15,412 --> 00:28:16,812
What?

295
00:28:18,845 --> 00:28:20,664
I was on a date...

296
00:28:21,678 --> 00:28:23,558
with your sister.

297
00:28:24,392 --> 00:28:27,012
She seemed in a hurry, so I came with her.

298
00:28:33,572 --> 00:28:36,965
You shouldn't call it a date.
He'll get the wrong idea.

299
00:28:36,965 --> 00:28:38,772
Sorry for joking like that...

300
00:28:39,292 --> 00:28:41,485
when you have a husband.

301
00:28:51,016 --> 00:28:53,182
I don't actually have a husband.

302
00:28:57,489 --> 00:28:58,889
I know.

303
00:29:00,202 --> 00:29:01,902
Is it that obvious?

304
00:29:04,496 --> 00:29:06,442
You're 36.

305
00:29:07,335 --> 00:29:08,948
<i>A doctor at SEAH Women's Hospital...</i>

306
00:29:08,948 --> 00:29:11,273
<i>You have your parents and a younger brother.</i>

307
00:29:11,273 --> 00:29:12,858
<i>You are 167cm tall,</i>

308
00:29:12,858 --> 00:29:16,288
<i>and your weight is...
a little more than I expected.</i>

309
00:29:21,428 --> 00:29:27,173
<i>Being pretty gets old after a couple of years.</i>

310
00:29:27,173 --> 00:29:29,673
<i>You see it everywhere.</i>

311
00:29:29,673 --> 00:29:30,777
<i>So this time...</i>

312
00:29:30,777 --> 00:29:32,397
<i>I already booked a room.</i>

313
00:29:34,873 --> 00:29:36,123
<i>At Cerati,</i>

314
00:29:36,123 --> 00:29:40,585
<i>there's an engine sound design team.</i>

315
00:29:40,585 --> 00:29:42,830
<i>A pianist and a composer...</i>

316
00:29:42,830 --> 00:29:45,226
<i>You want to sleep with me, huh?</i>

317
00:29:45,226 --> 00:29:47,339
<i>We just met today.</i>

318
00:29:47,339 --> 00:29:49,366
<i>It hasn't even been an hour.</i>

319
00:29:49,859 --> 00:29:51,310
<i>Hey...</i>

320
00:29:51,310 --> 00:29:52,596
<i>Lower your voice.</i>

321
00:29:52,596 --> 00:29:55,602
<i>Right, I guess that way we don't waste time</i>

322
00:29:55,602 --> 00:29:58,395
<i>and can tell if we're a match.</i>

323
00:29:59,699 --> 00:30:01,272
<i>Sorry.</i>

324
00:30:02,732 --> 00:30:04,233
<i>I'll pay.</i>

325
00:30:04,233 --> 00:30:06,651
<i>You wasted your time on a girl
you won't sleep with.</i>

326
00:30:06,651 --> 00:30:08,332
<i>No need to waste money too.</i>

327
00:30:09,013 --> 00:30:10,712
<i>You're rude till the very end.</i>

328
00:30:42,302 --> 00:30:44,322
It was a boring date,

329
00:30:45,049 --> 00:30:46,882
but you made it interesting.

330
00:30:48,528 --> 00:30:50,347
You were kind of impressive.

331
00:30:50,347 --> 00:30:52,867
The way you downed your drink
and just walked out.

332
00:30:52,867 --> 00:30:54,253
I'm not

333
00:30:54,253 --> 00:30:56,533
usually like that.

334
00:30:57,973 --> 00:30:59,373
Yeah?

335
00:31:00,579 --> 00:31:01,817
But...

336
00:31:01,817 --> 00:31:04,598
maybe I am.

337
00:31:11,887 --> 00:31:13,699
Want to listen to some music?

338
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:17,999
Something that boosts my confidence, please.

339
00:31:41,313 --> 00:31:42,874
Hold on a second.

340
00:32:03,357 --> 00:32:04,757
Thanks.

341
00:32:24,012 --> 00:32:26,445
Did you remember the door code?

342
00:32:40,644 --> 00:32:43,197
I'm glad I got a good neighbor like you.

343
00:32:45,722 --> 00:32:47,368
But what do we do?

344
00:32:48,242 --> 00:32:49,968
I won't be...

345
00:32:49,968 --> 00:32:51,928
your neighbor much longer.

346
00:32:54,127 --> 00:32:56,101
I'm moving soon.

347
00:33:00,116 --> 00:33:01,516
I see.

348
00:33:06,109 --> 00:33:07,982
That's a shame, right?

349
00:33:15,410 --> 00:33:16,917
Now...

350
00:33:17,437 --> 00:33:18,837
We probably won't...

351
00:33:23,050 --> 00:33:25,286
even run into each other anymore.

352
00:33:30,677 --> 00:33:32,810
How about we meet on purpose sometime?

353
00:33:59,790 --> 00:34:02,964
You booked a discounted rate,

354
00:34:02,964 --> 00:34:06,077
so the reservation is non-refundable.

355
00:34:08,157 --> 00:34:11,130
I'm sorry, but we can't offer a refund.

356
00:34:13,697 --> 00:34:15,410
As I said,

357
00:34:17,090 --> 00:34:19,950
there's no wife for me to go with anymore.

358
00:34:19,950 --> 00:34:22,870
I'm truly sorry,

359
00:34:23,950 --> 00:34:26,730
but there's nothing we can do.

360
00:34:33,442 --> 00:34:36,208
We wish you a good journey.

361
00:35:00,146 --> 00:35:02,757
That family always revolved around Julia.

362
00:35:02,757 --> 00:35:05,480
Their life, the children, everything.

363
00:35:05,480 --> 00:35:08,346
They raised them so fiercely, so well.

364
00:35:10,171 --> 00:35:13,582
I can't imagine how Raphael's managing
on his own now.

365
00:35:13,582 --> 00:35:16,034
It really worries me.

366
00:35:16,034 --> 00:35:17,066
Raphael?

367
00:35:17,066 --> 00:35:19,709
See you next time. Raphael?

368
00:35:19,709 --> 00:35:21,109
Raphael!

369
00:35:23,341 --> 00:35:25,274
Hello.

370
00:35:25,274 --> 00:35:30,108
I had something urgent
and couldn't make it to the funeral.

371
00:35:31,149 --> 00:35:32,935
It's okay.

372
00:35:32,935 --> 00:35:35,387
Julia held on for so long.

373
00:35:35,387 --> 00:35:38,388
It still doesn't feel real
that she's gone so suddenly.

374
00:35:40,975 --> 00:35:44,642
I heard it was a beautiful funeral.

375
00:35:44,642 --> 00:35:47,122
Just the right number of people.

376
00:35:47,122 --> 00:35:50,555
And they said
the priest's words were wonderful.

377
00:35:53,455 --> 00:35:55,928
Losing a spouse is supposed to be

378
00:35:55,928 --> 00:35:59,942
the most stressful thing
you can go through in life.

379
00:35:59,942 --> 00:36:02,628
Are you holding up?

380
00:36:04,595 --> 00:36:07,928
Please take this off. I don't need it.

381
00:36:11,129 --> 00:36:13,322
Poor thing.

382
00:36:49,441 --> 00:36:50,953
Hi, again.

383
00:36:50,953 --> 00:36:52,942
What are you doing here?

384
00:36:52,942 --> 00:36:54,932
Oh my! What the...

385
00:36:54,932 --> 00:36:56,935
What did you say earlier?

386
00:36:56,935 --> 00:36:58,412
"A beautiful funeral?"

387
00:36:58,412 --> 00:37:01,428
What's wrong with you?

388
00:37:02,508 --> 00:37:04,228
What kind of...

389
00:37:04,228 --> 00:37:06,093
funeral is beautiful?

390
00:37:06,093 --> 00:37:07,662
He must be insane.

391
00:37:07,662 --> 00:37:08,942
Oh, gosh!

392
00:37:08,942 --> 00:37:11,232
My goodness!

393
00:37:11,232 --> 00:37:12,905
Stop it!

394
00:37:21,799 --> 00:37:23,832
You're still here?

395
00:37:24,439 --> 00:37:27,386
You're okay, right?

396
00:37:28,086 --> 00:37:29,493
Yes.

397
00:37:29,493 --> 00:37:30,893
I'm fine.

398
00:37:31,579 --> 00:37:35,186
Julia will always be with you,
watching over you from heaven.

399
00:37:35,799 --> 00:37:37,786
- Thank you.
- Bye.

400
00:37:50,731 --> 00:37:52,411
You know...

401
00:37:52,411 --> 00:37:55,244
It hasn't been that long since my mom passed.

402
00:37:55,244 --> 00:37:58,237
Will it be okay to meet a guy
at a time like this?

403
00:37:58,237 --> 00:38:00,240
No one's ever going to...

404
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:02,374
show up right on cue and say,

405
00:38:02,374 --> 00:38:06,494
"Hey, now's the perfect time for you to date."

406
00:38:06,494 --> 00:38:08,311
I still can't believe that

407
00:38:08,311 --> 00:38:10,322
you gave your number to a stranger

408
00:38:10,322 --> 00:38:12,791
and not even a repair guy.

409
00:38:12,791 --> 00:38:13,960
For real?

410
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:15,551
No, it's just...

411
00:38:15,551 --> 00:38:17,361
when he said he was moving away,

412
00:38:17,361 --> 00:38:19,421
I panicked without even thinking.

413
00:38:19,421 --> 00:38:20,638
I must've lost my mind.

414
00:38:20,638 --> 00:38:23,378
You'll know once you meet him.

415
00:38:23,378 --> 00:38:25,691
He's not asking you to marry him
or have his kids.

416
00:38:25,691 --> 00:38:27,821
- It's just a date.
<i>- True.</i>

417
00:38:27,821 --> 00:38:29,221
Right?

418
00:38:30,728 --> 00:38:34,807
We did pick a place to meet. But...

419
00:38:36,641 --> 00:38:38,921
Wait, he's wearing a hoodie.

420
00:38:38,921 --> 00:38:40,181
A hoodie?

421
00:38:40,181 --> 00:38:41,488
Have they already met?

422
00:38:41,488 --> 00:38:44,086
Am I overdressed?

423
00:38:44,086 --> 00:38:45,586
<i>Hey, you never know.</i>

424
00:38:45,586 --> 00:38:47,610
He could be a hotshot startup CEO.

425
00:38:47,610 --> 00:38:49,351
Give me the phone.

426
00:38:49,885 --> 00:38:51,592
Hello, Jun Kyung.

427
00:38:51,592 --> 00:38:53,965
Don't just say whatever pops
into your head, okay?

428
00:38:53,965 --> 00:38:55,638
<i>Don't think too much.</i>

429
00:38:55,638 --> 00:38:57,835
<i>No, no. Just do whatever feels right.</i>

430
00:38:57,835 --> 00:38:59,775
Hang up. Bye.

431
00:39:02,476 --> 00:39:03,633
Are you listening?

432
00:39:03,633 --> 00:39:06,200
Hello? Hello?

433
00:39:06,200 --> 00:39:07,600
What?

434
00:39:08,146 --> 00:39:09,799
You were on a call, right?

435
00:39:11,200 --> 00:39:12,950
- Please...
- You were on a call, huh?

436
00:39:12,950 --> 00:39:14,373
Yeah.

437
00:39:25,003 --> 00:39:27,190
You're early.

438
00:39:27,190 --> 00:39:29,416
Yeah, I got here a bit ahead of time.

439
00:39:29,416 --> 00:39:33,189
This place gets crowded if we're late.

440
00:39:55,343 --> 00:39:56,367
It's a little awkward, right?

441
00:39:56,367 --> 00:39:57,769
Yeah?

442
00:39:58,774 --> 00:40:01,193
Yeah... kind of.

443
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:05,187
I guess it has to be.

444
00:40:05,187 --> 00:40:07,694
We've only run into each other
by chance before.

445
00:40:07,694 --> 00:40:09,686
This is our first real meeting.

446
00:40:17,092 --> 00:40:19,098
Isn't there anything you want to ask me?

447
00:40:20,031 --> 00:40:21,431
I do know...

448
00:40:22,112 --> 00:40:24,925
a bit about you though.

449
00:40:29,553 --> 00:40:30,973
I guess...

450
00:40:32,173 --> 00:40:35,019
I know a little about you too.

451
00:40:43,939 --> 00:40:45,339
Like...

452
00:40:49,385 --> 00:40:53,111
You seem younger than me.

453
00:40:55,970 --> 00:40:57,790
Around 35?

454
00:40:57,790 --> 00:41:00,117
And you're obviously not married.

455
00:41:00,117 --> 00:41:02,337
If you were, you wouldn't be here.

456
00:41:06,472 --> 00:41:09,218
As for what you do...

457
00:41:10,685 --> 00:41:12,518
I'm guessing something artistic.

458
00:41:13,112 --> 00:41:15,272
And probably not very lucrative.

459
00:41:15,272 --> 00:41:17,718
- How did you know?
- Wait, am I right?

460
00:41:26,946 --> 00:41:28,926
He is pretty a good man.

461
00:41:28,926 --> 00:41:31,333
He's kind of cute, in a way.

462
00:41:31,333 --> 00:41:32,733
But...

463
00:41:33,246 --> 00:41:36,603
He's 35 and still doing music.

464
00:41:36,603 --> 00:41:38,200
That feels a little...

465
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:40,553
It doesn't seem great as a job.

466
00:41:42,073 --> 00:41:44,393
What kind of music does he do?

467
00:41:45,940 --> 00:41:48,139
How should I put it...

468
00:41:49,540 --> 00:41:50,940
Just...

469
00:41:51,826 --> 00:41:53,846
A bit of everything.

470
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:57,166
I go with whatever I feel.

471
00:41:59,933 --> 00:42:01,986
I do anything and everything.

472
00:42:01,986 --> 00:42:03,979
He even knows what he does.

473
00:42:04,573 --> 00:42:06,152
Doesn't that remind you of someone?

474
00:42:06,152 --> 00:42:07,592
Who?

475
00:42:09,312 --> 00:42:12,792
A guy still stuck in his rebel phase,
long after everyone else grew out of it.

476
00:42:12,792 --> 00:42:15,486
Seo Jun Seo.

477
00:42:15,486 --> 00:42:18,386
- So he doesn't make money?
- You can tell just by looking.

478
00:42:19,626 --> 00:42:21,129
You should've asked things like,

479
00:42:21,129 --> 00:42:24,246
"what's your annual income?"

480
00:42:24,246 --> 00:42:26,257
"Can you support yourself?"

481
00:42:26,257 --> 00:42:27,750
"Are you a night owl?"

482
00:42:27,750 --> 00:42:29,650
"I'm totally a morning person."

483
00:42:29,650 --> 00:42:31,987
Stuff like that.

484
00:42:31,987 --> 00:42:33,590
What kind of guy asks,

485
00:42:33,590 --> 00:42:35,180
"How much do you weigh?"

486
00:42:35,180 --> 00:42:36,710
"What's your waist size?"

487
00:42:36,710 --> 00:42:40,277
"What's your body fat percentage?"
Would you answer that?

488
00:42:40,277 --> 00:42:42,200
- Yeah, I would.
- Totally.

489
00:42:42,200 --> 00:42:43,773
We're confident like that.

490
00:42:45,357 --> 00:42:47,343
I wish someone would ask me, too.

491
00:42:54,050 --> 00:42:56,096
He's lived that long, and yet...

492
00:42:58,163 --> 00:43:01,349
What did he give up
to have that kind of freedom?

493
00:43:01,936 --> 00:43:04,443
Money or status?

494
00:43:04,443 --> 00:43:05,943
Yeah.

495
00:43:05,943 --> 00:43:10,736
I don't think
I can handle that kind of freedom.

496
00:43:16,364 --> 00:43:17,843
Eat while it's hot.

497
00:43:23,058 --> 00:43:25,013
You burned your tongue, didn't you?

498
00:43:25,013 --> 00:43:26,321
It's hot.

499
00:43:26,321 --> 00:43:28,325
I just don't want to.

500
00:43:28,325 --> 00:43:30,290
Instead of trying to see

501
00:43:30,290 --> 00:43:33,978
what actually works between you two,

502
00:43:33,978 --> 00:43:38,632
you're digging up everything that doesn't.

503
00:43:38,632 --> 00:43:39,909
You're way too picky.

504
00:43:39,909 --> 00:43:42,407
I'm not digging. It's just obvious.

505
00:43:42,407 --> 00:43:43,760
Obvious how?

506
00:43:43,760 --> 00:43:45,447
Are you playing Tetris right now?

507
00:43:45,447 --> 00:43:49,807
Do you really think
someone will fit into all your gaps?

508
00:43:49,807 --> 00:43:51,657
You keep waiting for that long I-shaped block,

509
00:43:51,657 --> 00:43:52,743
and then it's game over.

510
00:43:52,743 --> 00:43:53,873
Do you really think

511
00:43:53,873 --> 00:43:57,560
someone will ever make her
fall for him like that?

512
00:43:57,560 --> 00:43:59,293
Rather than making her fall for him...

513
00:43:59,293 --> 00:44:01,413
Oh, it's empty.
She'd need a miracle to fall in love.

514
00:44:01,413 --> 00:44:02,670
Get us another drink.

515
00:44:02,670 --> 00:44:04,373
Give me a second.

516
00:44:06,220 --> 00:44:08,607
I thought you only dated guys

517
00:44:08,607 --> 00:44:11,527
if they were good-looking.

518
00:44:12,340 --> 00:44:14,087
I thought so too...

519
00:44:15,627 --> 00:44:18,340
But I'm more practical than I look.

520
00:44:24,207 --> 00:44:26,053
What's wrong?

521
00:44:28,713 --> 00:44:30,586
Is that really all?

522
00:44:37,520 --> 00:44:38,920
Actually...

523
00:44:42,473 --> 00:44:44,892
I was sure of one thing.

524
00:44:46,300 --> 00:44:47,926
About what?

525
00:44:49,260 --> 00:44:51,392
That you would...

526
00:44:53,693 --> 00:44:55,859
need me.

527
00:45:06,411 --> 00:45:08,497
I once heard that

528
00:45:09,351 --> 00:45:11,924
liking someone starts with...

529
00:45:13,151 --> 00:45:14,991
watching them.

530
00:45:19,118 --> 00:45:20,518
And I...

531
00:45:21,624 --> 00:45:23,024
I found myself...

532
00:45:24,264 --> 00:45:27,064
watching you without meaning to.

533
00:45:29,071 --> 00:45:30,991
Almost every day.

534
00:46:39,841 --> 00:46:41,707
You looked lonely.

535
00:46:44,061 --> 00:46:45,461
You.

536
00:46:47,301 --> 00:46:48,701
Like...

537
00:46:49,748 --> 00:46:52,134
You looked like someone...

538
00:46:52,908 --> 00:46:55,321
trying to be lonely.

539
00:46:57,801 --> 00:46:59,808
But, well...

540
00:46:59,808 --> 00:47:03,307
No one really chooses that on purpose.

541
00:47:16,423 --> 00:47:20,203
[Next Door Guy]

542
00:47:38,866 --> 00:47:41,455
Did you get home safely?

543
00:48:23,473 --> 00:48:24,873
Hello?

544
00:48:27,506 --> 00:48:29,672
Okay. Wait for me.

545
00:48:31,686 --> 00:48:33,472
Let's talk there.

546
00:48:47,230 --> 00:48:49,736
We ran into each other again.

547
00:48:58,358 --> 00:49:00,797
I couldn't reach you, so I was worried.

548
00:49:08,516 --> 00:49:11,122
Did I do something wrong last time?

549
00:49:12,296 --> 00:49:13,696
No.

550
00:49:14,529 --> 00:49:17,522
Was it the food we had? Was it bad?

551
00:49:28,993 --> 00:49:30,393
I thought...

552
00:49:31,626 --> 00:49:33,286
we felt pretty...

553
00:49:33,873 --> 00:49:35,739
natural together.

554
00:49:37,239 --> 00:49:39,559
Like we clicked.

555
00:49:43,662 --> 00:49:45,748
How do we click?

556
00:49:51,381 --> 00:49:52,921
Well...

557
00:49:52,921 --> 00:49:54,368
I mean...

558
00:49:54,368 --> 00:49:55,974
I thought we...

559
00:49:55,974 --> 00:49:58,480
could grow into it.

560
00:50:00,121 --> 00:50:02,480
Get to know each other more.

561
00:50:14,584 --> 00:50:16,077
Thinking about it now,

562
00:50:17,984 --> 00:50:20,198
your silence was an answer in itself.

563
00:50:24,559 --> 00:50:26,518
It's not just you.

564
00:50:28,198 --> 00:50:31,111
I don't want to get to know anyone.

565
00:50:49,246 --> 00:50:51,747
[Jeju Travel Voucher]

566
00:51:00,633 --> 00:51:02,926
Does this even make sense?

567
00:51:02,926 --> 00:51:04,080
Huh?

568
00:51:04,080 --> 00:51:06,020
You booked it to go with Mom.

569
00:51:06,020 --> 00:51:08,773
Then obviously you cancel it.

570
00:51:11,620 --> 00:51:14,080
Why don't you take Dad to Jeju instead?

571
00:51:14,080 --> 00:51:15,757
If you want to go, you go.

572
00:51:15,757 --> 00:51:17,973
- I have to work.
- I'm also busy.

573
00:51:19,520 --> 00:51:20,986
Jun Seo.

574
00:51:20,986 --> 00:51:23,233
- I...
- Aren't you sad at all?

575
00:51:23,793 --> 00:51:25,193
Huh?

576
00:51:28,618 --> 00:51:30,664
Why does no one seem sad?

577
00:51:31,251 --> 00:51:32,651
Why?

578
00:51:34,545 --> 00:51:36,164
I've been...

579
00:51:36,164 --> 00:51:38,168
since the day your mom had that accident...

580
00:51:38,168 --> 00:51:40,885
- for the past seven years...
- Are you happy now?

581
00:51:40,885 --> 00:51:43,798
You want to go to a hotel
and celebrate Mom's death?

582
00:52:31,393 --> 00:52:33,526
Hey, watch what you say.

583
00:52:40,455 --> 00:52:41,855
And you...

584
00:52:44,254 --> 00:52:47,255
What did you say to Mom before she died?

585
00:52:47,255 --> 00:52:48,685
You said she looked fat.

586
00:52:48,685 --> 00:52:52,161
I said her clothes looked tight.
I didn't call her fat.

587
00:52:53,551 --> 00:52:55,121
Don't you regret saying that?

588
00:52:55,121 --> 00:52:57,601
Being sad and feeling guilty
aren't the same thing.

589
00:52:57,601 --> 00:52:58,945
I'm asking if you regret it.

590
00:52:58,945 --> 00:53:00,861
What good does regret do?

591
00:53:02,534 --> 00:53:04,554
You should at least regret it.

592
00:53:18,954 --> 00:53:21,980
Is this what you meant by
"everyone grieves in their own way?"

593
00:53:23,227 --> 00:53:25,167
Yeah? You...

594
00:53:25,754 --> 00:53:28,501
You think everything was hard because of Mom?

595
00:53:28,501 --> 00:53:30,461
You're just like her.

596
00:53:30,461 --> 00:53:33,206
You both act like you're the only ones hurting.

597
00:53:33,206 --> 00:53:34,971
You're both selfish.

598
00:53:35,867 --> 00:53:37,267
But at least...

599
00:53:40,074 --> 00:53:42,947
Mom wasn't a coward like you.

600
00:53:55,765 --> 00:53:57,698
You ran away.

601
00:53:58,578 --> 00:54:01,251
You didn't move out because you were strong.

602
00:54:01,804 --> 00:54:04,250
You just wanted to escape this house, right?

603
00:54:13,988 --> 00:54:16,846
[Operating Room]

604
00:55:34,939 --> 00:55:36,339
Mom.

605
00:55:36,892 --> 00:55:38,292
Let's go to the hospital.

606
00:55:44,224 --> 00:55:45,678
Let's go together.

607
00:55:45,678 --> 00:55:47,078
I'm not going.

608
00:55:48,057 --> 00:55:50,004
You're not going to do rehab?

609
00:55:50,004 --> 00:55:52,564
How am I supposed to do rehab without legs?

610
00:55:56,752 --> 00:55:58,318
Fine.

611
00:55:59,085 --> 00:56:01,271
Even if you don't go to the hospital,

612
00:56:01,271 --> 00:56:04,385
you need to wash your face and your hair.

613
00:56:04,385 --> 00:56:06,565
Get up.

614
00:56:06,565 --> 00:56:07,965
No.

615
00:56:12,031 --> 00:56:14,518
Mom, are you giving up on life?

616
00:56:16,418 --> 00:56:18,538
Is this because of me?

617
00:56:18,538 --> 00:56:20,511
You think this happened because of me, right?

618
00:56:20,511 --> 00:56:22,862
So you're trying to fall apart
just to prove a point to me?

619
00:56:22,862 --> 00:56:24,855
- Get out.
- I told you not to come...

620
00:56:24,855 --> 00:56:27,979
- because it was raining!
- Get out! I said get out!

621
00:56:27,979 --> 00:56:29,797
Why did you come and do this to me?

622
00:56:29,797 --> 00:56:31,837
Get out!

623
00:56:45,831 --> 00:56:47,317
Jun Kyung.

624
00:56:50,777 --> 00:56:52,690
You can't just leave like this.

625
00:56:53,224 --> 00:56:55,997
Your mom's heart will ache.
Talk it out before you go.

626
00:56:58,657 --> 00:57:00,111
Later.

627
00:57:00,111 --> 00:57:01,937
Hey, Jun Kyung.

628
00:57:43,528 --> 00:57:46,214
I wanted to tell my past self

629
00:57:48,061 --> 00:57:49,914
not to let her go.

630
00:57:53,454 --> 00:57:55,460
I wanted to grab her

631
00:57:57,481 --> 00:57:59,254
and tell her to stop.

632
00:58:02,474 --> 00:58:05,014
If you run away now,

633
00:58:07,514 --> 00:58:10,247
you'll keep running forever.

634
00:58:12,801 --> 00:58:14,874
You'll keep pretending you're fine,

635
00:58:17,714 --> 00:58:19,894
and acting like nothing's wrong.

636
00:58:22,507 --> 00:58:23,907
You'll keep...

637
00:58:25,901 --> 00:58:27,301
You'll keep...

638
00:58:30,648 --> 00:58:32,048
being...

639
00:58:33,161 --> 00:58:35,014
alone.

640
00:59:24,356 --> 00:59:25,462
Yeah.

641
00:59:25,462 --> 00:59:27,462
<i>Are you drinking alone again?</i>

642
00:59:27,462 --> 00:59:29,502
We're about to open a bottle of wine.

643
00:59:29,502 --> 00:59:31,188
Come over to our place.

644
00:59:33,451 --> 00:59:34,957
Right...

645
00:59:37,231 --> 00:59:40,357
I always ran to your place.

646
00:59:42,517 --> 00:59:43,917
Pardon?

647
00:59:45,504 --> 00:59:47,397
<i>Maybe Hyeong Jun is right.</i>

648
00:59:47,397 --> 00:59:50,464
I don't think I can do anything on my own.

649
00:59:51,924 --> 00:59:53,695
I can't fight.

650
00:59:53,695 --> 00:59:55,610
I can't make up.

651
00:59:56,617 --> 00:59:59,970
I can't comfort anyone... or be comforted.

652
01:00:05,667 --> 01:00:07,426
The only thing I can do alone

653
01:00:08,147 --> 01:00:09,919
is be lonely.

654
01:00:13,986 --> 01:00:15,527
Hey.

655
01:00:15,527 --> 01:00:17,253
Do you want me to come over?

656
01:00:28,398 --> 01:00:29,798
No.

657
01:00:32,004 --> 01:00:33,404
It's okay.

658
01:00:37,313 --> 01:00:38,713
I'm okay tonight.

659
01:00:50,472 --> 01:00:51,906
Jun Kyung?

660
01:00:54,540 --> 01:00:55,940
Sorry.

661
01:01:00,827 --> 01:01:02,227
Huh?

662
01:01:06,334 --> 01:01:08,227
There's nothing for you

663
01:01:08,227 --> 01:01:10,227
to apologize for.

664
01:01:12,777 --> 01:01:14,336
I mean...

665
01:01:22,976 --> 01:01:24,482
Well...

666
01:01:27,403 --> 01:01:28,803
You mean what?

667
01:01:32,803 --> 01:01:34,809
I wasn't being honest.

668
01:01:45,143 --> 01:01:48,589
I always hide how I feel and lie about it.

669
01:01:54,715 --> 01:01:56,228
So...

670
01:01:57,548 --> 01:01:59,101
I mean...

671
01:02:03,655 --> 01:02:05,855
I want to get to know you.

672
01:02:20,601 --> 01:02:22,167
Weren't you the one

673
01:02:25,749 --> 01:02:28,415
who said you didn't want to get to know anyone?

674
01:02:33,403 --> 01:02:35,329
I want to try.

675
01:02:38,663 --> 01:02:40,909
If it's not too late.

676
01:02:49,045 --> 01:02:51,031
It's late now.

677
01:02:56,299 --> 01:02:58,359
But I think there's still a chance.

678
01:03:13,321 --> 01:03:15,514
So... what do we do now?

679
01:03:18,315 --> 01:03:19,715
Well...

680
01:03:21,668 --> 01:03:23,647
Let's take it slow.

681
01:03:26,601 --> 01:03:28,315
Okay.

682
01:03:28,315 --> 01:03:29,715
Slowly.

683
01:03:38,195 --> 01:03:40,235
Do you want to come in for a bit?

684
01:03:47,076 --> 01:03:48,476
No.

685
01:03:49,903 --> 01:03:51,303
Slowly.

686
01:03:52,470 --> 01:03:53,923
Okay.

687
01:03:55,463 --> 01:03:56,863
Slowly.

688
01:04:36,222 --> 01:04:40,182
<i>I portioned the beef soup
and put it in the freezer.</i>

689
01:04:40,182 --> 01:04:43,639
<i>Don't skip meals,
and make sure you lock the door.</i>

690
01:04:51,945 --> 01:04:54,457
<i>Yoon Sol, you nailed it today.</i>

691
01:04:55,251 --> 01:04:56,638
<i>Did you fall for me?</i>

692
01:04:56,638 --> 01:04:58,570
"Fall for me?"

693
01:04:58,570 --> 01:04:59,725
What the...

694
01:04:59,725 --> 01:05:01,978
- I'm Joo Hyun Kyung.
- I see.

695
01:05:01,978 --> 01:05:03,704
Nice to meet you.

696
01:05:07,554 --> 01:05:09,147
Mr. Seo Jin Ho?

697
01:05:09,912 --> 01:05:11,459
Yeah, that's me.

698
01:05:12,153 --> 01:05:15,439
Is Mrs. Kim Mi Ran not coming?

699
01:05:16,472 --> 01:05:17,824
Well...

700
01:05:17,824 --> 01:05:19,965
There's something going on.

701
01:05:21,006 --> 01:05:23,037
Would it be okay if I went alone?

702
01:05:23,906 --> 01:05:25,392
<i>Life...</i>

703
01:05:27,631 --> 01:05:30,079
<i>never lets either its brightest blessings</i>

704
01:05:32,227 --> 01:05:34,507
<i>or its deepest sorrows</i>

705
01:05:36,714 --> 01:05:40,027
<i>stay with us for long.</i>

706
01:05:41,847 --> 01:05:44,129
<i>More than crushing sorrow,</i>

707
01:05:44,129 --> 01:05:45,154
What is this?

708
01:05:45,154 --> 01:05:48,521
<i>it's the anger that makes
my heart race that matters to me.</i>

709
01:05:48,521 --> 01:05:50,014
That's interesting.

710
01:05:50,014 --> 01:05:51,841
Sorry?

711
01:05:51,841 --> 01:05:54,548
I've never seen anyone
wear dress shoes on a trip.

712
01:05:54,548 --> 01:05:56,521
<i>More than crushing sorrow,</i>

713
01:05:59,021 --> 01:06:00,045
You look cool.

714
01:06:00,045 --> 01:06:04,394
<i>those small, unexpected flutters
matter more in our lives.</i>

715
01:06:08,082 --> 01:06:10,488
<i>They never let either bright blessings</i>

716
01:06:13,509 --> 01:06:15,842
<i>or crushing sorrow</i>

717
01:06:21,051 --> 01:06:22,690
<i>stay with us</i>

718
01:06:25,624 --> 01:06:27,490
<i>for long.</i>

719
01:06:29,804 --> 01:06:31,970
<i>That's life.</i>

720
01:07:12,968 --> 01:07:14,451
- A house party?
- Yes.

721
01:07:14,451 --> 01:07:17,148
How about we have my birthday at your place?

722
01:07:17,148 --> 01:07:20,814
Is this what you meant by
everyone grieving in their own way?

723
01:07:20,814 --> 01:07:23,780
I'm a total lost cause.

724
01:07:24,401 --> 01:07:26,041
I'm glad you came.

725
01:07:26,041 --> 01:07:27,854
That's good for you.

726
01:07:27,854 --> 01:07:30,641
It feels like I'm the only one
living well without her.

727
01:07:30,641 --> 01:07:32,327
It makes me feel so guilty...

728
01:07:32,327 --> 01:07:33,961
and it hurts so much.

729
01:07:33,961 --> 01:07:35,874
Mr. Seo?

730
01:07:35,874 --> 01:07:37,121
Are you okay?

731
01:07:37,121 --> 01:07:38,146
We said...

732
01:07:38,146 --> 01:07:40,646
we'd take it slow, right?

733
01:07:41,374 --> 01:07:42,999
Is it really that good?

734
01:07:42,999 --> 01:07:44,058
I knew it.

735
01:07:44,058 --> 01:07:46,687
When one becomes two, things get complicated.

736
01:07:47,174 --> 01:07:49,858
You won't regret getting to know me, will you?

737
01:07:49,858 --> 01:07:52,931
I'm going crazy, wondering
why I ever liked you,

738
01:07:52,931 --> 01:07:55,147
why I trusted someone like you.

